{"book":"1 Corinthians","chapter":12,"questions":[{"id":"1cor-12-q1","type":"multiple_choice","question":"What metaphor does Paul use to describe the church and its members?","options":["A family","A body with many parts","An army","A garden"],"answer":"A body with many parts","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 12:12"},{"id":"1cor-12-q2","type":"multiple_choice","question":"Who distributes spiritual gifts, according to Paul?","options":["The apostles","Church leaders","The Holy Spirit","Each person chooses their own"],"answer":"The Holy Spirit","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 12:11"},{"id":"1cor-12-q3","type":"true_false","question":"Paul says all members of the body have the same function.","answer":"false","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 12:17-20"},{"id":"1cor-12-q4","type":"fill_blank","question":"Now you are the body of Christ, and each one of you is a _____ of it.","answer":"member","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 12:27"},{"id":"1cor-12-q5","type":"fill_blank","question":"If one member suffers, all the members _____ with it.","answer":"suffer","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 12:26"}]}
